\[\frac{[AOB]}{[O_1 O_2]} = \frac{\theta}{2 \pi}.\]Furthermore,
\[\frac{[AOB]}{[O_1 O_2]} = \frac{[ACD] + [BDC]}{[O_1 O_2]} = \frac{[ACD]}{[O_1 O_2]} + \frac{[BDC]}{[O_1 O_2]}.\]Let $r$ be the common radius of the circles.  Then
